{
  "texts": [
    "(This short notation shall mean that the two summands are the only active circles, both of multiplicity one, i.e.",
    "mapped to 1 by the irregular class Θ.)",
    "There are four singular directions, and hence any Stokes local system with irregular class Θ is determined by four Stokes factors and the formal monodromy.",
    "Explicitly, if we choose a base point b ∈ ∂ and a framing at b, the Stokes data of any connection with irregular class Θ are of the form:",
    "and must satisfy hS 4 S 3 S 2 S 1 = id."
